longBusinessSummary: Grupo Radio Centro, S.A.B. de C.V., a radio broadcasting company, engages in the production and transmission of musical and entertainment programs, information and analysis programs, news, and special events in Mexico and the United States. It operates through Radio and Television Station segments. The company owns and operates AM and FM radio stations in Mexico city, Guadalajara, Iguala, Monterrey, and Oaxaca. It also operates Organización Impulsora de Radio, a national channel, which acts as a national sales representative and provides programming services in Mexico. Grupo Radio Centro, S.A.B. de C.V. was founded in 1946 and is based in Mexico City, Mexico. Grupo Radio Centro, S.A.B. de C.V. is a subsidiary of GRC, SA de CV.
